Package management commands
*************************************************
In package management we using either dnf or yum 

>For installing the package 
   yum install package -y

>For removing the package
   yum remove package -y

>For update the package 
   yum update -y   

>For search the package 
   yum search package

>For information about the package 
    yum info package

>To check the list installed package 
    yum list installed

>To check the update
    yum check-update

>To clear the stored package data
    yum clean all

>To reinstall the package
    yum reinstall package -y

>To list all available packages
    yum list available 

>Display the all dependies of the package
    yum deplist package

>To install specific version package
    yum install package-version

>Shows the all past install remove and update package [transaction history] 
    yum history

>To revert the previous oprations of using its transaction id
    yum history undo <id>

>To read the same operation again
    yum history redo <id>

>Check the history package install versions dependies and view details of the transacton
    yum history info <id>    

>To know the package how many times installed 
    yum history |grep package
    
    yum history list git
>to check the package source 
    yum list packsge    

<REPOSITORY MANAGEMENT>:
*****************************************
> List of all enable repositories
   yum repolist

>List all enabled and disable repositories
   yum repolist all

>To enable the disable repository
   yum config-manager --set-enable repo-name

>Disable the enanble repository
  yum config-manager --set-disable repo-name

>To see full details of repository 
   yum repoinfo

>To see all disabled repository
  yum repolist disabled

>Install the package at pariticular repository
   yum install package --enablerepo=repo-name

>disable the package temporarliy at a particular repository
   yum install package --disablerepo=repo-name

GROUP MANAGEMENT COMMANDS: 
>list of all groups
