RPM COMMANDS:
*******************************
one command with many options

rpm -ivh --nodeps --replacepkgs --test package.rpm

-i=install(to install the .rpm package)
v=verbous (to give the detailed information)
h=hash(show the progress bar)
nodeps=ignore the dependies checking
relacepkgs=to reinstall the package if already installed
test=to test the package

>To install the package 
  rpm -ivh package.rpm

>To give single line information installed package
  rpm -q package-name

>To give detailed information about installed package
  rpm -qi package-name

>to upgrade package manually 
  rpm -Uvh package.rpm

